# Plan + subagent orchestration (from-thesis-to-paper / fttp)

Apply when the user asks to **create a plan**, **get subagent prompts**, or **run part of a plan** — unless they say “no subagents” or “solo en este chat”.

## User intent → agent behavior (default)

| User says | Agent does | Agent does **not** do (unless explicit override) |
|-----------|------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| “Haz un plan para …” | Phase A: **slim** plan file (DoD, topology, launch map, subagent map) — **no** full prompt dumps inside `.plan.md` | Auto-launch subagents; embed 26 prompts in plan unless user asks |
| “Dame los prompts” / “prompt N” / “Guía de ejecución” | Phase C: **Guía first**, then copy-paste `text` blocks **in chat** (or optional sidecar `.cursor/plans/<slug>_prompts.md` if user asks to save) | Summarize prompts; skip Guía |
| “Dame el prompt del subagente N” / “prompts en orden” | Deliver copy-paste block(s) for requested step(s) only | Run other steps |
| “Ejecuta SA3” / pastes one subagent prompt | Run **that scope only** in current chat; closure protocol | Advance to SA4 without user OK |
| “Ejecuta el plan X” | **Interpret as:** show launch map + offer prompt 1 (or next pending). User launches each chat. | Batch-launch 8 workers silently |
| “Ejecuta el plan completo sin preguntar” / Multitask + explicit batch | May delegate via Task tool in background | Skip handoff blocks |
| Small fix, one file | Normal single-session work | Force subagent decomposition |

**Default control model:** the **user** decides how many subagents to launch and when. The **agent** decides **how many subagents the plan needs** and **which steps are sequential, parallel, or async**.

Override batch execution only when the user uses an explicit phrase like *“lanza todos los subagentes”* or Multitask with that intent.

---

## Topology types (agent must label each block)

| Type | Symbol | Meaning | Launch rule |
|------|--------|---------|-------------|
| **Sequential** | `→` | Step B needs output or artifacts from step A | Launch B only after A reports **SE TERMINÓ LA TAREA COMPLETA** |
| **Parallel** | `∥` | Steps share no write paths; same precondition | User may open 2+ chats at once; merge before next sequential gate |
| **Async** | `~>` | Step can start anytime; **no** input from other steps (read-only audit, docs, figures on fixed paths) | User may run early or late; note in plan if it **must** finish before a gate (then mark parallel or sequential instead) |

Every plan must include a **Launch map** section, e.g.:

```text
1 → 2 → 3 → (4 ∥ 5) → 6 → 7 → 8
     async optional: 11 ~> after 3 (figures; no main.tex edits)
```

Use mermaid in the plan file when more than 3 nodes.

---

## Agent criteria: how many subagents (N)

The agent **proposes N** in the plan (not the user). Guidelines:

| Factor | More subagents | Fewer subagents |
|--------|----------------|-----------------|
| Domains | Python + LaTeX + docs split | Same file family |
| Risk | pytest/build gates between stages | Read-only audit |
| Context | &gt; ~40 lines or &gt;3 files per scope | One script + one test file |
| Model strength | Weaker executor expected | Strong single session OK |

**Target N:** usually **4–10** for multi-phase work; **1–3** for medium tasks; **never** split a single-file fix.

**Merge rule:** combine SAs that touch the same files in sequence (e.g. SA1+SA2 code+tests). **Split rule:** separate read-only preflight (async) from writers; separate LaTeX Results from LaTeX Intro if parallel after tables exist.

Document in plan: **“Recomendación: N subagentes porque …”**

